Experiment 26
 Minimal CGI Example in C


Aim:

To write a minimal CGI program using C that generates simple dynamic HTML output when executed through a web server supporting CGI.


Algorithm

1. Start the program.
2. Include the required header <stdio.h> for input/output.
3. Inside main():
Print the HTTP header:
Content-Type: text/html
Print a blank line to separate header from body.
Print simple HTML content such as <html>, <body>, and a message.
4. Compile the program and save the executable in the serverâ€™s cgi-bin directory.
5. Execute the program through a web browser.
6. The browser displays the HTML generated by the CGI program.
7. End the program.


Program:

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    // Required HTTP header
    printf("Content-Type: text/html\n\n");
    // HTML output
    printf("<html>\n");
    printf("<head><title>Minimal CGI Example</title></head>\n");
    printf("<body>\n");
    printf("<h2>Hello! This is a Minimal CGI Program.</h2>\n");
    printf("</body>\n");
    printf("</html>\n");

    return 0;
}


Output :
Hello! This is a Minimal CGI Program.
Displayed inside formatted HTML:
Browser Output:
Hello! This is a Minimal CGI Program.


Result

The minimal CGI program is successfully implemented.
The program prints the correct HTTP header followed by HTML code, and the output is displayed through a web browser using a CGI-supported server.
This demonstrates how C can be used to generate simple dynamic web content using the Common Gateway Interface (CGI) mechanism.
